  I had anotehr thougth about hiring employees and freeelancers for b0ase.com LTD. too. We need to pioneer a new model, one where we empower our employees to work using a claude-code max plan x20 ($200/month) in an IDE like Antigravity or Cursor. I want to use these specific tools to get everyone aligned so that they can take ownership of the development pipeline and develop out the business using the same tools that I use. 
  AI agents can be used to do the heavy lifting for many tasks, but having a human in the loop who is paid to push the tasks forward is useful and also, they can push development intiatives on their own which agents cannot. 
  Thought abotu rightly: An employee or freelancer, could be a founder and a developer, using the b0ase.com platform to develop and launch their ideas allows b0ase.com to take a small slice of equity in whatevr they decide to push out. 
  This gives employees a lot of autonomy, but it does mean sacrificying pure operational freedom since it would mean having to put in place processes for simulataneously developmetn with other users UNLESS we can develop the system enough at the /user/account level that they can simply use all the features of the platform without changing its fundamental architecture. 
